Our Aim

To develop a Question-Answering system, specifically designed for students, that can answer basic questions ranging from academics, sports to placements at IIT Roorkee

Broad Categories of Questions

  • Academics
  • Sports
  • Hostels
  • Mess
  • Events
  • Internships and Placements

 Datasets used/Data Sources and QA

The dataset comprises of two test files:

 

  • database.txt - Contains set of questions
  • ans.txt - Contains corresponding answers

 

The dataset is generated manually.

Libraries Used

  • NLTK (Natural Language Toolkit, Python)
  • SKLearn (Scikit-Learn, Python)
  • Numpy (Python)
  • Stanford POS Tagger (Java)
  • Stanford NER Tagger (Java)
  • PyEnchant (English dictionary, Python)

Modules of the project

1. Question Type Classifier

2. Focus Words Extraction

3. Similarity Maximisation of Question

4. Ranking of Answers according to relevance

5. Feedback System

Question type Classifier

Understanding the intent of the question helps in finding accurate answers.

Categories:

  • Human
  • Description
  • Number
  • Entity
  • Abbreviation
  • Location

Intent Classification Accuracy

Focus Words Extraction

The focus words are the most important words in a sentence. To extract the focus words we make use of the ‘Stanford POS Tagger’ and ‘Stanford NER Tagger’.

 

Example Sentence: Who is the director of IIT Roorkee?

Focus Words: director, iit, roorkee

Similarity Maximization of Question

We use focus words to find the similarity score for each question in our database, then extract the questions with the maximum similarity score. 

Similarity Maximisation Example

Ranking of Answers according to relevance

We may have a situation in which we may have multiple questions with the same similarity score.

 

To rank the answers according to relevance we find the question whose answer is most similar to the question asked.

Feedback System

The user may not always be satisfied with the answer. This feature helps in the dynamic improvement of the system, without interfering with the old preprocessed data.

Feedback System example

Results

Single Answer Accuracy = 60% If we only take the top answer as the output, it will give correct output 60% of the time.

 

Top-3 Answers Accuracy = 70% Taking top-3 answers as our output, our accuracy score improves by 10%.

Challenges / Future Work

  • Insufficient Data

  • Optimal Weights in Bag-of-Words representation

  • Capturing the semantic meaning of question

  • Using more efficient similarity measures

Word2vec

  • Given an input word, outputs a vector representation of the word in a high dimensional space
  • e.g. "college" maps to [5, 0, 1, 3,  0]
  • Captures the semantic context of a word
  • but requires sufficiently large dataset to train
